body:
I'm testing this code in OPPO A71, Nougat
Now i want to set this launcher as default launcher from this app but it minimize the app and nothing happened
Here is your DefaultLauncherPreference code:

`  Context context = getContext();

            // get packet manager
            PackageManager packageManager = context.getPackageManager();
            // get dummyActivity
            ComponentName componentName = new ComponentName(context, DummyActivity.class);
            // enable dummyActivity (it starts disabled in the manifest.xml)
            packageManager.setComponentEnabledSetting(componentName, PackageManager.COMPONENT_ENABLED_STATE_ENABLED, PackageManager.DONT_KILL_APP);

            // create a new (implicit) intent with MAIN action
            Intent intent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_MAIN);
            // add HOME category to it
            intent.addCategory(Intent.CATEGORY_HOME);
            // launch intent
            context.startActivity(intent);

            // disable dummyActivity once again
            packageManager.setComponentEnabledSetting(componentName, PackageManager.COMPONENT_ENABLED_STATE_DISABLED, PackageManager.DONT_KILL_APP);`

# Symptoms
The overall interface becomes unusable, the lists flickers while the icons are blank, the favourites can't be launched.

# Possible cause
Kiss started to behave weirdly after the following scenario have been followed:

* Received a vCard by SMS into Signal sent from an iPhone 11.3;
* Called the number shown in the vCard data by clicking on the hyper-link in the message;
* Finished the call;
* Hit the Â«Home ButtonÂ» to get back to Kiss which behaves normally;
* Opened the phone app again;
* Started to create a new entry in the address book for the number;
* Closed the new entry to check if the contact already exists;
* Selected Â«add to existing contactÂ»;
* Browsed to the entry and selected the entry for the mobile phone;
* Saved and hit home to get back to Kiss which immediately started to behave weirdly;
* No error message is showing.

# Failed attempts to solve the problem
* Rebooting the phone;
* Changing the default launcher to the stock one and then back to Kiss;
* Removing the screen protection;
* Thoroughly cleaning the screen;
* Cleaning the memory and processes.


# Circumventing the problem
* Unselecting the contacts option in the Data Source menu in Kiss' parameters makes it behaves normally again;
* Reselecting this entry puts Kiss back in an unstable status;

# Next steps

I'm waiting for your feedback, in the case you'd like to have a log trace in buggish state.

* Deleting the entry;
* Purging Kiss history;
* Uninstalling Kiss to install it back.

# Context

* app version : Kiss 3.2.0 from F-Droid repo
* android version: 8.0.0 on EMUI 8.0.0 published by Huawei, no kernel mods (i.e. rootâ€¦)
* device used: Huawei Mate 9 (MHA-L29)
* custom settings that might have an impact: none to my knowledge.
* one or more screenshot: can't screenshot, problem appear to be dynamic, not static.

Cheers, PAH.

I uploaded three drawables (**setting_accessibility**, **setting_dev** and **setting_memory**) to be used with the new settings.

I also updated the **LoadSettingsPojos.java** in order for the three settings to use the appropriate drawables.

@Neamar Please **disregard any file out of the abovementioned, if possible**. Only the above were in fact updated.

Pressing the keyboard has no action.

